          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MAGSP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The multiple-gap spectrograph consists of 25",
                "gaps that permit simultaneous analysis of charged",
                "particles from the target. These gaps are located every",
                "7.5 deg from zero through 172.5 deg with respect to the",
                "direction of the incident beam."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "PLATE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The 50 mu Eastman NTA photographic plates,",
                "which were used with the multiple-gap spectrograph to",
                "detect the protons, were covered with a layer of",
                "aluminum sufficiently thick to stop the elastically and",
                "inelastically scattered deuterons."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EDE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "The measured resolution E/dE over this whole range",
                "was approximately 1000 or better, which corresponds to",
                "a half-width of <= 12 keV for the proton groups."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A 46Ti target was prepared by the retardation method to",
                "more than 99% relative purity. The backing was a carbon",
                "foil approximately 50 mu-g/cm2 thick. The area of the",
                "carbon backing onto which the 46Ti material was",
                "deposited measured approximately 2 mm *1 mm."
              ]
            }
          ],
